mindX agents/eval/ — evaluation framework for mindX self-awareness
====================================================================

Portions of this package are adapted from confident-ai/deepeval
(https://github.com/confident-ai/deepeval), licensed under Apache License 2.0.

Specifically:
  - The GEval algorithm (criteria → evaluation_steps → judge prompt →
    {score, reason} → normalization) follows the design in
    deepeval/metrics/g_eval/. The judge prompt template in g_eval.py
    is adapted from deepeval/metrics/g_eval/template.py:GEvalTemplate.
  - The BaseMetric contract (measure / a_measure / threshold / score /
    reason / success / is_successful) follows
    deepeval/metrics/base_metric.py.
  - The LLMTestCase shape (input / actual_output / expected_output /
    context / retrieval_context / metadata) is a slim subset of
    deepeval/test_case/llm_test_case.py.

The GEval algorithm itself is from:
  Liu et al., "G-Eval: NLG Evaluation using GPT-4 with Better Human
  Alignment," arXiv:2303.16634 (2023).

Modifications from upstream:
  - Replaced DeepEvalBaseLLM with a thin adapter over mindX's
    llm/llm_factory.create_llm_handler() returning generated text and
    optional log-probabilities.
  - Removed: pytest harness, Confident-AI cloud upload, OpenTelemetry,
    posthog, sentry, multimodal/MCP/conversational machinery, the
    metric_progress_indicator UI, the Pydantic structured-output
    pipeline (replaced with permissive JSON parsing).
  - Async-only — no sync measure() implementation. mindX is
    async-throughout.
  - Log-probability reweighting is a stub (Ollama does not expose
    OpenAI-shaped logprobs). Hook is in place for future cloud judges.

Apache-2.0 license terms are preserved. Each ported file carries an
attribution header. Upstream LICENSE applies to adapted portions.
